{{more citations needed|date=May 2011}} [[Image:Hurricane Michael (2000).jpg|thumb|right|300px|[[Hurricane Michael (2000)|Hurricane Michael]] shortly before making landfall in [[Harbour Breton]], Newfoundland as a [[post-tropical cyclone]] on 20 October 2000.]] There have been 25 recorded '''Newfoundland hurricanes''',<!-- "Hurricane" is a generic term for a tropical cyclone in the Atlantic Ocean, so tropical depressions and storms can also be included on this list. --> or Atlantic [[hurricane]]s that have made a direct landfall as a [[Tropical cyclone|tropical]] or [[subtropical cyclone]] on the island of [[Newfoundland (island)|Newfoundland]] since official records began in 1851. Significant hurricanes such as the [[1775 Newfoundland hurricane]] are also included on this list, even though they occurred prior to the start of official record-keeping.
