{{Expand list|date=April 2016}} {{No footnotes|date=September 2016}}
[[Aquatic plant]]s are used to give the [[aquarium]] a natural appearance, oxygenate the [[water]], and provide [[Habitat (ecology)|habitat]] for [[fish]], especially [[Fry (biology)|fry]] (babies) and for [[invertebrate]]s. Some aquarium fish and invertebrates also eat live plants. Hobby [[aquarist]]s use aquatic plants for [[aquascaping]].
[[Marine algae]] are also included in this list for convenience, despite the fact that many species are technically classified as [[protists]], not plants.
